## 🌍 The Problem

Pakistan has **33 million diabetics** — the **3rd highest in the world.**

Over **50% remain undiagnosed.**

Community health workers running rural screening camps have no fast intelligent triage tool. They screen hundreds of patients manually with no way to prioritize who needs urgent referral.

**GlucoseGuard PK changes that.**

---

## 🩺 What It Does

GlucoseGuard PK is a Machine Learning web application designed for community health workers and NGO screening camps across Pakistan.

| Feature | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| 🎯 Risk Prediction | Instant diabetes risk score (%) from basic health indicators |
| 🟢🟡🔴 Risk Classification | Clear Low / Medium / High risk levels |
| 🔍 SHAP Explainability | Top 5 risk drivers explained in plain language |
| 📋 Referral Guidance | Lifestyle advice / Retest / Refer for HbA1c |
| 👥 Population Summary | Camp-level screening insights for NGOs |

---

## 📊 Machine Learning Pipeline

| Stage | Details |
|-------|---------|
| Dataset | CDC BRFSS 2015 — 80,000+ health records |
| Models Evaluated | Logistic Regression, Random Forest, XGBoost |
| Selected Model | Logistic Regression |
| Key Metric | Diabetic Recall: **76%** |
| Class Imbalance | Handled with SMOTE |
| Explainability | SHAP LinearExplainer |
| Deployment | Streamlit Cloud |

### 🤔 Why Logistic Regression?

For a health screening tool, **missing a diabetic patient is dangerous.**

Logistic Regression achieved **76% recall on diabetic cases** compared to XGBoost's 18% — making it the clinically safer choice for triage support.

